### λμηιτ

I've started working on a new xUnit test framework that uses the new lambda syntax in Java 8.
The inspiration comes from the Javascript test framework [Jasmine](http://pivotal.github.io/jasmine/),
so this is what it looks like:

```
        describe("A suite", (d) -> {
            it("contains spec with an expectation", (o) -> {
                expect(true).toBe(true);
            });
        });
```

At present it kind of works, but it's still an early experiment.

### To Do

* nested describes
* a separate test runner
* before, after and afterEach
* more than two matchers
* handling of exceptions thrown by test case
